article.headline: Portland St. 94, Sacramento St. 66
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. -- Jamie Jones scored a career-high 26 points and grabbed 13 rebounds to lead Portland State to a 94-66 win over Sacramento State on Saturday night. Dominic Waters also scored 26 points for the Vikings (7-7, 2-0 Big Sky) while Phil Nelson added 18. Duro Bjegovic led the Hornets (6-10, 1-3) with 17 points, and John Dickson had 12. Portland State trailed 14-11 eight minutes into the game before hitting four unanswered 3-pointers during a 12-0 run that gave it a 23-14 advantage with 9:21 left in the half. The Vikings put the game away in the second half and led 70-50 after Waters capped a 9-0 run with a layup with 9:31 to play. Portland State connected on 13-of-27 3-pointers, outrebounded Sacramento State 43-25 and shot 54 percent to the Hornets' 41 percent.
